The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | WI put Lanka in to bat 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     WI put Lanka in to bat 
                      
	Port of Spain: The West Indies won the toss and invited Sri Lanka to bat in the second one-day International at Queens Park Oval on Saturday. Sri Lanka replaced Ishara Amerasinghe with Kaushalya Weeraratne. The West Indies have brought in Daren Powell and Denish Ramdin replaces Patrick Browne as wicketkeeper. West Indies lead 1-0 in the three match series.         
	Teams         
	Sri Lanka: Mahela Jayawardene (captain), Kumar Sangakkara, Tillakaratne Dilshan, Chaminda Vaas, Chamara Silva, Nuwan Kulasekara, Chamara Kapugedera, Ajantha Mendis, Upul Tharanga, Mahela Udawatte, Kaushalya Weeraratne         
	West Indies: Chris Gayle (captain), Sewnarine Chattergoon, Ramnaresh Sarwan, Marlon Samuels, Shivnarine Chanderpaul, Dwayne Bravo, Darren Sammy, Denesh Ramdin, Jerome Taylor, Daren Powell, Fidel Edwards (Reuters)                                                                                                                          
